        <h2>Aspirin</h2>
        <p>Aspirin is a nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drug (NSAID) used to treat pain, fever, and inflammation. It works by inhibiting the production of prostaglandins, which are chemicals in the body that promote inflammation, pain, and fever.</p>
