        <p>Omeprazole is a proton pump inhibitor (PPI) medication used to reduce the production of stomach acid and treat conditions such as heartburn, acid indigestion, and gastroesophageal reflux disease (GERD). It works by blocking the enzyme in the stomach lining that produces acid.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <h2>Lisinopril</h2>
        <p>Lisinopril is an angiotensin-converting enzyme (ACE) inhibitor medication used to treat high blood pressure (hypertension), heart failure, and improve survival after a heart attack. It works by relaxing blood vessels, which lowers blood pressure and improves blood flow.</p>
    </li>
